title.narrative: Integrated Maternal, Neonatal, Child Health and Nutrition / Family Planning Regional Project in Mindanao (MindanaoHealth)

description.narrative: (Philippines): The MindanaoHealth Project will support the scale-up and institutionalization of DOH-led high-impact practices to reduce maternal and infant deaths, and meet the demand for family planning services. It will focus in geographic areas with high unmet need for family planning and high teenage pregnancy rates. It will support the implementation of the Executive Order on reducing unmet need for family planning services, and institutionalize existing technical initiatives. USAID will use FY 2017 funds to bolster local partners' capacity to institutionalize good practices, strengthen service delivery networks and family planning in hospitals, enhance health providers' skills, expand PhilHealth accreditation, strengthen the reporting system, conduct supportive supervision, and regularly conduct data quality checks. It will also support a rapid health assessment, risk communication strategy, and restoration of basic FP/MCH health services in areas vulnerable to violent extremism.
